author: COMSOL
description: This example simulates atmospheric general corrosion of steel under a droplet of aqueous sodium chloride solution. The model accounts for mass transport together with homogeneous reactions and atmospheric oxygen and carbon dioxide interactions. The model computes the transient and spatial distribution of species within the droplet, including passivating corrosion products formed in precipitation reactions at the electrode surface.
